<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2018-12-17</DATELINE><TITLE>Development of Small-Molecule MERS-CoV Inhibitors</TITLE><BODY>Middle East respiratory syndrome coronavirus (MERS-CoV) with potential to cause global pandemics remains a threat to the public health, security, and economy. In this review, we focus on advances in the research and development of small-molecule MERS-CoV inhibitors targeting different stages of the MERS-CoV life cycle, aiming to prevent or treat MERS-CoV infection.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>